.\" Manpage for slot_machine
.TH SLOT_MACHINE 1 "2025-12-15" "1.0" "Slot Machine Game"
.SH NAME
slot_machine \- text-based slot machine game

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B slot_machine
[\-h]

.SH DESCRIPTION
.B slot_machine
is a terminal-based slot machine game written in C. The player starts with a fixed number of credits
and can place bets to spin the reels. Matching symbols increase credits according to the payout rules.

The game supports UTF-8 symbols for reels and displays a simple 3x3 reel matrix.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-h, --help
Show help message and exit.

.SH GAMEPLAY
After launching the game:

.RS
.IP
You are prompted to enter a bet amount.  
.IP
Enter a numeric value between 1 and your current credits, or 'q' to quit.  
.IP
The reels will spin and display the outcome.  
.IP
Payout rules:
.RS
.IP
Three matching symbols: win 5× bet
.IP
Two matching symbols: win 2× bet
.IP
No match: lose the bet
.RE
.IP
Press Enter to continue after each spin.
.RE

.SH CREDITS
You start with 100 credits.

.SH EXAMPLES
To start the game:

.EX
$ ./slot_machine
.EX

.SH FILES
.PP
The program uses gettext PO files for localization in the ./po directory.

